OL,3,CSpeeding drug-driver jailed after
OL,4,Ckilling grandma on mobility scooter
OL,6,FMrs Raynor's eldest living son,
OL,7,FMichael Raynor, described his mother's
OL,8,Fdeath as "tragic and senseless".
OL,10,FHe said: "Your reckless and
OL,11,Firresponsible decision to drive under
OL,12,Fthese conditions shattered our family
OL,13,Fand left a gaping hole in the lives of
OL,14,Fall who had known her."
OL,16,FDefending Middleton, Simon Eckersley
OL,17,Fsaid: "Plainly she was going too fast.
OL,18,FHad she been travelling at an
OL,19,Fappropriate speed, there still would
OL,20,Fhave been a collision, but a collision
OL,21,Fwith less impact.
